examples.en: Slow and steady wins the race.
We've had two wins so far this season.
Three wins in a row ignited the team.
The team has an equal number of wins and losses.
The team has had a long streak of wins.
He will support whichever candidate wins.
Their record was 3 wins, 6 losses and a tie.
The team with the highest aggregate score wins.
He draws all the trumps and wins all the tricks.
If he wins today, he's on course for the Grand Slam.
The team now has an amazing record of 43 straight wins.
Don't play (at) cards against your father, he always wins.
Two wins at the start of the season were a foretaste of things to come.
Whichever team wins on Saturday will go through to the national championships.
Often presentation wins out over content (=is treated as more important than content).
In the auction buyers bid up the price until one buyer, by virtue of entering the high bid, wins.
